    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen ui2 is enabled and opt.title is set to true, “[Pager]” shows up in the terminal title when a file loads, and it disappears after pressing “:”.\n\n<img width=\"306\" height=\"45\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/28a1163a-4f2f-444a-8d48-9516043184cd\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`init.lua`\n\n```lua\nrequire('vim._core.ui2').enable()\nvim.opt.title = true\n```\n\nThen load any file.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nJust the title.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal 1.24.10921.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n-\n\n### Installation\n\nGithub Release",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
