            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Indeed, I bisected it to 56709ca1. Not sure how that commit affected it, but I think Nvim should prevent updating the title while renaming a buffer that is not the actual current buffer. This seems to work:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/api/buffer.c b/src/nvim/api/buffer.c\nindex 7ab9f20360..614fcc4ebd 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/api/buffer.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/api/buffer.c\n@@ -962,22 +962,11 @@ void nvim_buf_set_name(Buffer buf, String name, Error *err)\n \n   int ren_ret = OK;\n   TRY_WRAP(err, {\n-    const bool is_curbuf = b == curbuf;\n-    const int save_acd = p_acd;\n-    if (!is_curbuf) {\n-      // Temporarily disable 'autochdir' when setting file name for another buffer.\n-      p_acd = false;\n-    }\n-\n     // Using aucmd_*: autocommands will be executed by rename_buffer\n     aco_save_T aco;\n     aucmd_prepbuf(&aco, b);\n     ren_ret = rename_buffer(name.data);\n     aucmd_restbuf(&aco);\n-\n-    if (!is_curbuf) {\n-      p_acd = save_acd;\n-    }\n   });\n \n   if (ERROR_SET(err)) {\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/autocmd.c b/src/nvim/autocmd.c\nindex a5c6be1d06..330c890598 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/autocmd.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/autocmd.c\n@@ -1301,6 +1301,12 @@ void aucmd_prepbuf(aco_save_T *aco, buf_T *buf)\n     aco->save_prompt_insert = curbuf->b_prompt_insert;\n   }\n \n+  // Prevent changing working directory and updating title.\n+  aco->save_acd = p_acd;\n+  aco->save_title = p_title;\n+  p_acd = false;\n+  p_title = false;\n+\n   if (win != NULL) {\n     // There is a window for \"buf\" in the current tab page, make it the\n     // curwin.  This is preferred, it has the least side effects (esp. if\n@@ -1332,14 +1338,10 @@ void aucmd_prepbuf(aco_save_T *aco, buf_T *buf)\n       pmap_put(int)(&window_handles, auc_win->handle, auc_win);\n       win_config_float(auc_win, auc_win->w_config);\n     }\n-    // Prevent chdir() call in win_enter_ext(), through do_autochdir()\n-    const int save_acd = p_acd;\n-    p_acd = false;\n     // no redrawing and don't set the window title\n     RedrawingDisabled++;\n     win_enter(auc_win, false);\n     RedrawingDisabled--;\n-    p_acd = save_acd;\n     unblock_autocmds();\n     curwin = auc_win;\n   }\n@@ -1465,6 +1467,8 @@ win_found:\n     }\n   }\n \n+  p_acd = aco->save_acd;\n+  p_title = aco->save_title;\n   VIsual_active = aco->save_VIsual_active;\n   check_cursor(curwin);  // just in case lines got deleted\n   if (VIsual_active) {\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/autocmd_defs.h b/src/nvim/autocmd_defs.h\nindex f11a40743c..bbb8a0ca0c 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/autocmd_defs.h\n+++ b/src/nvim/autocmd_defs.h\n@@ -21,6 +21,8 @@ typedef struct {\n   char *globaldir;                ///< saved value of globaldir\n   bool save_VIsual_active;        ///< saved VIsual_active\n   int save_prompt_insert;         ///< saved b_prompt_insert\n+  int save_acd;                   ///< saved p_acd\n+  int save_title;                 ///< saved p_title\n } aco_save_T;\n \n typedef struct {\n```",
